als einzig rechtmäßiger Nachfolger des 1910 von Japan
annektierten Kaiserreichs Korea. Nordkorea wollte die
Wiedervereinigung Koreas unter eigener Führung erzwingen.

Korea was ruled by Japan from 1910 until the closing
days of World War II. In August 1945, the Soviet Union
declared war on Japan and—by agreement with the United
States—occupied Korea north of the 38th parallel.
U.S. forces subsequently occupied the south and Japan
surrendered. By 1948, two separate governments had been set
up. Both governments claimed to be the legitimate government
of Korea, and neither side accepted the border as permanent.
The conflict escalated into open warfare when North Korean
forces—supported by the Soviet Union and China—invaded
South Korea on 25 June 1950.

